a bonus is a lump-sum payment that is not a permanent increase to the base salary of the individual and may be granted at the discretion of the president. these bonuses are taxable and do not count toward retirement benefits. a bonus may be given monthly for an identified period of time or may be done as a one-time transaction. only an appropriate administrator may request a bonus. it is important to review the appropriate collective bargaining agreement(s) for the valid reasons a bonus may be given. it is critical to make the criteria for earning a bonus known to all employees once approved by classification & compensation. mpp bonuses are required to use non-state funds. to initiate an mpp bonus, the request to process classification and/or compensation transaction form will need to be submitted and approved. request to process classification and/or compensation transactions [docusign]  contact classcomp@sjsu.edu to review the criteria and discuss the appropriate steps to take to announce and grant a bonus. at the decision of the campus president or designee, an employee may receive a monthly stipend when assigned, for a limited period of time, additional work or special projects over and above their regularly assigned duties or required to maintain contact with their campus outside of their normal working hours on a regular basis. please note, only employees in uapd, csueu and supa are eligible for stipends. the request for a stipend should be submitted and approved the additional work is assigned. to initiate a stipend, the request to process classification and/or compensation transaction form will need to be submitted and approved. university-personnel@sjsu.edu up north: 408-924-2450 up south: 408-924-2250  up webmaster up north administration building 242 up south upd building 3rd floor 